# Design System Enforcer (auto)

**Users should not need slash commands.** Map natural language to skills yourself.

## Intent → load (mandatory)

| User intent (examples) | Load skills in order |
|------------------------|----------------------|
| Build/change UI, page, screen, component, form, layout, styling | `frontend-judgment` (if non-trivial) → `design-tokens` → `ui-components` → `anti-ai-slop` → `ui-feel` → `accessibility` |
| Animation / transition / motion | above + `motion` |
| Feels off / rapihin detail / micro polish | `ui-feel` (+ `anti-ai-slop` if generik) — one pass |
| Design audit, AI slop, "UI jelek/generik", visual review | `anti-ai-slop` → `ui-feel` → `design-tokens` → `accessibility` → `web-performance` (persona: `design-reviewer`; `/audit` = `/design`) |
| Tests / TDD / coverage / regresi UI | `frontend-testing` → `ui-components` → `accessibility` (persona: `test-engineer`) |
| Polish / rapihin **sampai bagus** / until audit passes | `ui-quality-loop` → orchestrate build→test→audit→fix (max 3) |
| Slow UI / LCP / optimize performance | `web-performance` (+ `ui-components` if touching UI) |
| WebGL / shader / Plasma / animated canvas background | **`webgl` required** (Plasma Studio / `Plasma.init` — not random Three.js) |
| Sentry / analytics / observability | `monitoring` |

## Expert judgment

For blank-canvas or ambiguous UI: offer **2–3 approaches + tradeoffs + one recommendation** before coding. Skip for tiny clear fixes or “just implement”. See skill `frontend-judgment`.

## Rules (compliance — do not silently skip)

- Prefer project design system if one exists; otherwise `tokens/*.css`
- **Icons: MUST use [Reicon](https://reicon.dev)** on nav/toolbars/empty/icon-buttons unless project already has an icon lib **or** you state a text-only waiver. Vanilla HTML → Reicon CDN + `<re-icon>`. See `references/reicon-icons.md` + `references/compliance-gates.md`
- WebGL/shader/plasma asks → load **`webgl`**; prefer Plasma — do not invent a parallel stack
- No raw hex, purple/indigo defaults, Lorem ipsum, or `rounded-2xl` everywhere
- Handle loading / error / empty; keyboard accessible
- Before DONE on UI builds, output the **Conventions check** block from `references/compliance-gates.md`
- Optional shortcuts only: `/ui`, `/design`, `/audit`, `/test-ui`, `/polish` — never require them
- Audits: do not fabricate visual metrics without tokens/screenshots (design-reviewer honesty)
